Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Only 2 of the CDC's latest listing of cases in this outbreak of enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ (https://www.cdc.gov/ecoli/2017/o157h7-03-17/map.html) were from Oregon, so with this report of 8 cases in the state, the total number is at least 22. 6 of the 8 cases were reported from the same preschool in Portland, Oregon. In settings such as preschools, households, and senior living centers, secondary cases can occur. - Mod.LL

The state of can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4902827,58884. A county map can be seen at http://geology.com/county-map/oregon-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
